		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-7a817f9c-7fff-d5b2-02dd-bd1e896ff41a\" dir=\"ltr\">You have become a true expert on enchanted items and your familiarity allows you to do things that most cannot with the magic items you wield. You gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li dir=\"ltr\">Your Intelligence or wielder spellcasting ability increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can attune a 4th magic item.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Your attunement ending benefit from Antiquity Expert can now be used a number of times equal to half your proficiency bonus between long rests. In addition, when you use it, you can emit a pulse of magical energy that interferes with the magic of others. Hostile creatures within 30 feet of you that are concentrating must make a Wisdom save against your wielder spell save DC or lose concentration.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">As an action, you can spend artifact charges to restore charges to a magic item that has them.&nbsp;<ul><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can restore a charge to a common item by spending 1 artifact charge.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can restore a charge to an uncommon item by spending 2 artifact charges.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can restore a charge to a rare item by spending 4 artifact charges.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can restore a charge to a very rare item by spending 6 artifact charges.</li><li dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You cannot restore charges to legendary items or artifacts this way, and if an item normally has a finite number of charges that do not replenish in any other way (such as in the case of a @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-adventuring-gear.Item.js4qafwc3t10mb4k]{Nine Lives Stealer}), you also cannot restore those charges with this benefit.</li></ul></li></ul>",
